on/stories/2006/09/18/daily70.html |title=Hard Rock signs lease for Faneuil Hall space |last= Kooker|first=Naomi |date=September 22, 2006 |website= www.bizjournals.com|access-date=2019-10-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| <s>[[Acapulco]]</s>\n| Mexico\n| Closed\n| {{dts|December 8, 1989}}\n| {{dts|January 17, 2014}}\n| \n|-\n| [[Washington, D.C.]]\n| United States\n| Open\n| {{dts|January 1, 1990}}\n| \u2014\n| \n|-\n| [[Singapore]]\n| Singapore\n| Open\n| {{dts|February 6, 1990}}\n| \u2014\n| \n|-\n| [[Orlando, Florida|Orlando]]\n| United States\n| Open\n| {{dts|June 7, 1990}}\n| {{dts|December 11, 1998}}\n| [[Universal CityWalk]] complex, Relocated\n|-\n| <s>[[Maui]]</s>\n| United States\n| Closed\n| {{dts|July 23, 1990}}\n| {{dts|December 31, 2016}}\n|  \n|-\n| <s>[[Las Vegas]] at [[Hard Rock Hotel and Casino (Las Vegas)|Hard Rock Hotel]]</s>\n| United States\n| Closed\n| {{dts|September 7, 1990}}\n| {{dts|January 01, 2017}}\n| \n|-\n| <s>[[Montreal]]</s>\n| Canada\n| Closed\n| {{dts|September 20, 1990}}\n| {{dts|September 27, 2009}}\n| \n|-\n| <s>[[Puerto Vallarta]]</s>\n| Mexico\n| Closed\n| {{dts|December 30, 1990}}\n| {{dts|August 7, 2011}}\n| \n|-\n| <s>[[Aspen, Colorado|Aspen]]</s>\n| United States\n| Closed\n| {{dts|January 22, 1991}}\n| {{dts|November 1, 2000}}\n| \n|-\n| [[Bangkok]]\n| Thailand\n| Open\n| {{dts|April 22, 1991}}\n| \u2014\n| \n|-\n| [[Kuala Lumpur]]\n| Malaysia\n| Open\n| {{dts|November 9, 1991}}\n| \u2014\n| \n|-\n| [[Paris]]\n| France\n| Open\n| {{dts|November 24, 1991}}\n| \u2014\n| \n|-\n| [[Osaka]]\n| Japan\n| Open\n| {{dts|January 17, 1992}}\n| {{dts|September 14, 2001}}\n| Relocated\n|-\n| <s>[[Tijuana]]</s>\n| Mexico\n| Closed\n| {{dts|April 26, 1992}}\n| {{dts|June 19, 2008}}\n| \n|-\n| [[Berlin]]\n| Germany\n| Open\n| {{dts|May 18, 1992}}\n| {{dts|April 26, 2010}}\n| \n|-\n| [[Jakarta]]\n| Indonesia\n| Open\n| {{dts|October 2, 1992}}\n| -\n| Originally lobster at Sarinah Plaza. Relocated to Plaza Indonesia Entertainment X'nter in July 2004. Cur