a]] ([[Kanata, Ontario|Kanata]])\n| Canada\n| Open\n| {{dts|January 15, 1996}}\n| \u2014\n| Hard Rock Caf\u00e9 closed on August 8, 2002.<br/>'''Hard Rock Club''' bar announced in 2018.<ref name=\"HardRockClub\"/>\n|-\n| [[Surfers Paradise, Queensland|Surfers Paradise]]\n| Australia\n| Open\n| {{dts|March 22, 1996}}\n| \u2014\n| Originally called Gold Coast. \n|-\n| <s>[[Ottawa]]</s>\n| Canada\n| Closed\n| {{dts|June 26, 1996}}\n| {{dts|September 1, 2013}}\n| [[Rideau Carleton Raceway]] to become '''Hard Rock Ottawa''' in 2021.\n|-\n| [[Niagara Falls, New York|Niagara Falls]]\n| United States\n| Open\n| {{dts|July 10, 1996}}\n| \u2014\n| \n|-\n| <s>[[Shanghai]]</s>\n| China\n| Temp. Closed\n| {{dts|August 2, 1996}}\n| {{dts|December 26, 2016}}\n| Closed March 21, 2004. Relocated but temporarily closed\n|-\n| <s>[[Guangzhou]]</s>\n| China\n| Closed\n| {{dts|September 2, 1996}}\n| {{dts|May 18, 2003}}\n| \n|-\n| [[Key West, Florida|Key West]]\n| United States\n| Open\n| {{dts|September 27, 1996}}\n| \u2014\n| \n|-\n| [[Atlantic City, New Jersey|Atlantic City]]\n| United States\n| Open\n| {{dts|November 15, 1996}} \n| {{dts|June 28, 2018}}\n| Closed September 30, 2017 as part of the [[Hard Rock Hotel & Casino Atlantic City]] improvements plan. Restaurant originally opened as part of the Trump Taj Mahal, it remained open (independently operated) after the hotel and casino's closure until current round of construction began as part of conversion with its new owners. Relocated June 28, 2018. \n|-\n| [[Cape Town]]\n| South Africa\n| Open\n| {{dts|November 22, 1996}}\n| {{dts|October 11, 2017}}\n| Closed June 17, 2001. Relocated\n|-\n| <s>[[Seoul]]</s>\n| South Korea\n| Closed\n| {{dts|December 2, 1996}}\n| Unknown\n| Closed January 1, 2007. Reopened in April 18, 2008 but closed again in April 2009. Reopened in October 21, 2014.\n|-\n| [[Niagara Falls, Ontario|Niagara Falls Canada]]\n| Canada\n| Open\n| {{dts|December 9, 1996}}\n| \u2014\n| \n|-\n| <s>[[Beirut]]</s>\n| Leba