ro Dnipropetrovsk|Dnipro Dnepropetrovsk]]\n| relegated          = [[FC Neftchi Baku|Neftchi Baku]]<br />[[FC Kairat Almaty|Kairat Alma-Ata]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[1989\u201390 European Cup|Champions League]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[Dnipro Dnipropetrovsk|Dnipr Dniprotervosk]]\n| continentalcup2    = [[1989\u201390 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[1988\u201389 Soviet Cup|Torpedo Moscow]]\n| continentalcup3    = [[1989\u201390 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]]<br />[[Dynamo Kyiv|Dynamo Kiev]]<br />[[FK \u017dalgiris|\u017dalgiris Vilnius]]<br />[[Zenit Leningrad]]\n| league topscorer   = (16) [[Aleksandr Borodyuk]] ([[Dynamo Moscow]]), [[Yevhen Shakhov (footballer, born 1962)|Yevgeniy Shakhov]] ([[Dnipro Dnipropetrovsk|Dnipro Dneprotervosk]])\n| biggest home win   = \n| biggest away win   = \n| highest scoring    = \n| matches            = \n| total goals        = \n| longest wins       = \n| longest unbeaten   = \n| longest losses     = \n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason = [[1987 Soviet Top League|1987]]\n| nextseason = [[1989 Soviet Top League|1989]]\n}}\n\n==Teams==\n===Promoted teams===\n* [[FC Chornomorets Odesa|FC Chernomorets Odessa]] \u2013 champion ''(returning after a seasons)''\n* [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow]] \u2013 2nd place ''(returning after seven seasons)''\n\n===Location===\n{{OSM Location map\n| float        = center\n| width        = 700\n| height       = 500\n| coord        = {{coord|52.0|50.0}}\n| mark-coord   = {{coord|46.466667 |30.733333}} |label = Chernomorets |label-pos = left  | mark = Red pog.svg  | label-color = blue\n| mark-coord1  = {{coord|50.45     |30.523333}} |label1 = Dynamo K     |label-pos1 = left  | mark1 = Red pog.svg  | label-color1 = blue\n| mark-coord2  = {{coord|40.183333 |44.516667}} |label2 = Ararat       |label-pos2 = right | mark2 = Red pog.svg  | label-color2 